      "Porn whispers to partners that they are inadequate—not attractive enough, not exciting enough, not enough. This is a lie designed to isolate and wound, and it works with devastating effectiveness.",
      "If your partner uses porn, their behavior is not a verdict on your worth. Porn use is driven by neurological compulsion, not by genuine dissatisfaction with you. The people on those screens are not competitors—they are props in an addictive cycle.",
      "Partners of porn users often experience symptoms that mirror trauma: intrusive thoughts, hypervigilance, loss of trust, and profound grief. This is real, and it deserves real support—not minimization.",
      "You are enough. You have always been enough. What your partner is struggling with is theirs to own and theirs to fight. And there is help—for them, and for you. You don't have to navigate this alone.",
    ],
